# Token Economics

Full policy: `docs/TOKEN_ECONOMICS.md`

## Cursor vs API keys

- **Cursor included models:** coding, refactors, tests, architecture, parsers, provider plumbing only.
- **User API keys (via Python scripts):** bulk analysis, synthesis, bibles, comment clustering — NOT Cursor chat at scale.

Do not suggest pasting hundreds of reports or thousands of comments into Cursor for analysis.

## Model routing (when implementing LLM layer)

| Workload | Provider |
|----------|----------|
| Bulk classification, tagging, clustering | DeepSeek (or local) |
| Final synthesis (bibles, personas, cross-channel) | Claude — **summary input only** |
| Prompt engineering, plans, taxonomies | GPT |
| Trend / competitor research | Grok — sparingly |
| Pipeline steps 1–11 today | Local only — no API |

## Forbidden

- Premium LLM (Claude/GPT-4 class) on large-scale classification
- Claude reading full raw comment dumps or all reports without DeepSeek compression first
- Hardcoded provider calls in step modules — use `channel_analyzer/llm/` abstraction + `config.yaml` `llm:`
- Uncached repeat synthesis of the same artifacts

## Required pattern

```
Raw artifacts → DeepSeek extraction → structured JSON → Claude synthesis → cached artifact
```

## Every new LLM call must

1. Estimate tokens and rough cost
2. Cache under `artifacts/llm_cache/`
3. Log provider + model in output metadata
4. Update `docs/CURRENT_STATE.md` when wired

## Config

Use `config.yaml` → `llm:` block (PLANNED until implemented). See `docs/TOKEN_ECONOMICS.md`.
